<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Columbus 4, Dallas 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Jeff Cunningham had a goal and an assist  
as the Columbus Crew beat the Dallas Burn 4-1 in Major League 
Soccer Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Cunningham put Columbus up 2-0 after collecting a shot by Stern  
John that ricocheted off Dallas defender Eric Dade and shooting it 
past Burn goalkeeper Matt Jordan in the 42nd minute. It was his 
seventh goal of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 50th minute, Cunningham sent a cross at the top of the  
box to John, who scored on a left-foot shot to make it 3-0. Crew 
defender Mike Lapper also assisted on the play. 
</P>
<P>
	Ansil Elcock opened the scoring for the Crew off a corner kick  
by Robert Warzycha. Jason Farrell assisted on the play by heading 
the corner to Elcock, who headed it past Jordan in the 28th minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Brian West put the Crew up 4-0 in the 71st minute off an assist  
by Brian Maisonneuve. 
</P>
<P>
	Ted Eck scored for Dallas in the 90th minute after Maisonneuve  
tried to head away a cross inside the box, but instead sent it to 
Eck. Eck put it past Crew goalkeeper Mark Dougherty. 
</P>
<P>
	The Crew outshot the Burn 17-10 and 9-5 in shots on goal.  
</P>
<P>
	The Crew scored a season-high four goals despite playing without  
forward Brian McBride, who played Saturday with the national team 
in a Confederations Cup game against New Zealand. 
</P>
<P>
	Columbus closed to within four points of D.C. United in the  
Eastern Conference. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
