<HEADLINE> Rays Put Alvarez on Disabled List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Devil Rays on Saturday  
placed pitcher Wilson Alvarez on the 15-day disabled list, 
retroactive to July 18, with left triceps inflammation. 
</P>
<P>
	Alvarez is the team's major league-leading 22nd player on the DL  
this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Alvarez was scratched from his scheduled start Thursday against  
the New York Yankees. The left-hander was also on the DL from April 
12-28 with left shoulder inflammation. 
</P>
<P>
	Tampa Bay filled Alvarez's spot by recalling pitcher Alan Newman  
from Triple-A Durham. 
</P>
<P>
	The Devil Rays also announced that pitcher Scott Aldred is the  
player to be named in a July 20 trade with the Philadelphia 
Phillies that sent pitcher Marty Barnett to Tampa Bay. 
  	   	
