<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Santerre Races to 1st NASCAR Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. (AP) -- Andy Santerre, last season's  
rookie of the year, got his first NASCAR Grand National victory 
Saturday, holding off Tim Fedewa by less than a second to win the 
NAPA AutoCare 250 at Pikes Peak International Speedway. 
</P>
<P>
	Todd Bodine finished third, followed by Jeff Green and Jeff  
Purvis. 
</P>
<P>
	Santerre, making only his third season start because of a broken  
leg suffered at Daytona in February, took the lead for good 16 laps 
from the end when he put his Chevrolet ahead of the Chevy driven by 
Dale Earnhardt Jr., the leader in the season driver standings. 
</P>
<P>
	``When I saw the checkered flag, I didn't know what to do,''  
Santerre said. ``I just pushed the button (two-way radio) and 
started screaming. I was pretty excited. 
</P>
<P>
	``He (Earnhardt) picked up the throttle early trying to beat me,  
but I think he tried to pick the throttle right back up and got up 
a little too high. Then I still thought he'd come back by me on the 
outside, but he didn't. 
</P>
<P>
	``When I got up in front of him, I knew I got the line then.''  
</P>
<P>
	Earnhardt was involved in a crash with 11 laps left that dropped  
him to a 36th-place finish and cost him the points lead. Matt 
Kenseth, who finished seventh, improved to 2,786 points, 24 ahead 
of Earnhardt. 
</P>
<P>
	Dave Blaney, who started from the pole, was involved in a late  
accident that dropped him to 24th. 
</P>
<P>
	``They've had an awfully tough year, the injury,'' Fedewa said  
of Santerre's broken leg. ``People just don't realize just how 
serious his injury was. He was out for several months, and the 
rehabilitation he had to go through, and not knowing if he is going 
to be able to make it back.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
