<HEADLINE> Garofalo 'Apathetic' About Stardom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Known in Hollywood for dressing down, Janeane  
Garofalo is proud to say she just doesn't care, even if that means 
she'll never be a major movie star. 
</P>
<P>
	``It wouldn't happen,'' Garofalo says in the July 30-Aug. 1  
issue of USA Weekend magazine. ``You have to have a lot more 
dedication to what I'll call the machine. I have 20 percent 
dedication. What's needed is 110 percent. You can't have it with 
the level of apathy I have.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 34-year-old character actress is known for her work in such  
films as ``The Truth About Cats &AMP; Dogs,'' ``Copland'' and ``Reality 
Bites.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Garofalo, known for her casual clothes and makeup-free style,  
was ridiculed by Joan Rivers and other media fashion mavens after 
the 1996 Emmy Awards for wearing a plain, off-the-rack dress to the 
ceremony. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's a let-them-eat-cake quality to the fashion that  
bothers me,'' Garofalo said. ``I can't in good conscience read in 
the paper about a Bosnian rape camp and then put on an $8,000 
Versace dress.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
