<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Braves' Smoltz Off Disabled List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The Atlanta Braves reinstated right-hander  
John Smoltz from the 15-day disabled list and designated 
right-hander John Hudek for assignment on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Smoltz, sidelined with a strained right elbow, was scheduled to  
make his 16th start of the season against the Philadelphia Phillies 
on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	He was 8-3 with a 3.49 ERA before going on the disabled list  
July 5. He made two rehab appearances at Double-A Greenville. 
</P>
<P>
	Smoltz was on the disabled list with the same injury from May 17  
to June 1. When he returned, Smoltz went 4-3 with a 4.76 ERA before 
going back on the disabled list. 
</P>
<P>
	Smoltz began the year in stellar fashion as he went 4-0 with a  
1.51 ERA in his first five starts, earning him NL pitcher of the 
month honors. 
</P>
<P>
	Hudek compiled an 0-1 mark with a 6.48 ERA in 15 games after  
being acquired by the Braves. The right-hander struggled with his 
control, walking 11 and allowed 21 hits in 16 2-3 innings. 
  	   	
</P>
