<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Boating Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Two pleasure boats, one without its  
lights on, slammed into each other on the Ohio River, killing at 
least two people and injuring two more in a late-night accident, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Divers on Saturday used sonar in the murky, 30-foot-deep water  
to search for two more possible victims. 
</P>
<P>
	The crash occurred about 11:30 p.m. Friday when the river was  
still crowded with boaters out on excursions on the hot, muggy 
night. 
</P>
<P>
	``There were two boats, one going upriver and one downriver,  
that had a head-on collision,'' said Officer Aaron Graham, a 
Louisville police spokesman. ``We know that the downriver boat did 
not have its running lights on, and that may be a contributing 
factor.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Both victims were from the boat without lights and police  
believe there may have been up to four people on board. That boat 
was ripped apart on impact and sank. 
</P>
<P>
	It was not immediately known if alcohol was a factor.  
  	   	
</P>
