<HEADLINE> WNBA Suspends Player for Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Cleveland's Tracy Henderson was suspended for  
two games and four Detroit players were disciplined for their roles 
in a fight during the Rockers-Shock WNBA game Friday night, the 
league announced Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Tracy Henderson was also fined $2,000 for fighting.  
</P>
<P>
	Detroit's Dominique Canty and Val Whiting were each suspended  
for one game and fined $1,000, and Astou Ndiaye was given a 
one-game suspension and $500 fine for leaving the vicinity of the 
bench. Detroit's Cindy Brown also was fined $750 for helping 
initiate the altercation. 
</P>
<P>
	The fight took place with 5:24 remaining in the game. Henderson,  
Whiting and Brown were ejected from the game and Detroit coach 
Nancy Lieberman-Cline was given a technical foul. 
</P>
<P>
	Detroit beat the Rockers 69-60.  
  	   	
</P>
