<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tour de France Glance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FUTUROSCOPE, France (AP) -- A look at Saturday's 19th stage of  
the 86th Tour de France: 
</P>
<P>
	STAGE: A 35-mile time trial around the science and technology  
park at Futuroscope. 
</P>
<P>
	STAGE WINNER: Lance Armstrong with a time of one hour, eight  
minutes, 17 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	HOW OTHERS FARED: Switzerland's Alex Zulle was second, with  
American Tyler Hamilton in third. 
</P>
<P>
	OVERALL STANDINGS: Armstrong holds a commanding 7:37 lead over  
Zulle, with Fernando Escartin dropping from second to third. 
</P>
<P>
	TOUR TIDBITS: Armstrong has now won all three of the Tour's time  
trials: the prologue, the eighth stage and now the 19th stage. 
</P>
<P>
	He acknowledged he might not be in this position if Alex Zulle,  
the Swiss rider now in second place, hadn't lost crucial minutes 
early in the Tour when he got caught behind a crash on a roadway 
crossing the water. 
</P>
<P>
	QUOTE OF THE DAY: ``It would have been easy to put in 90 percent  
effort today. But I wanted to show that the yellow jersey is the 
strongest cyclist in the race,'' Armstrong said. 
</P>
<P>
	NEXT STAGE: Sunday, the final 89-mile leg from Arpajon to the  
Champs-Elysees in Paris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
