<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stottlemyre Eyes August for Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Barring any complications, Todd Stottlemyre will  
return to the Arizona Diamondbacks' pitching rotation on Aug. 18 in 
a home game against the Chicago Cubs. 
</P>
<P>
	Diamondbacks manager Buck Showalter, Stottlemyre and the team's  
medical staff met Friday night and established a tentative 
timetable for the right-hander's rehabilitation that includes two 
simulated games in the coming days, followed by three starts in the 
minors. 
</P>
<P>
	Team doctor David Zeman said Stottlemyre has made a remarkable  
recovery from the torn rotator cuff, an injury that occurred May 17 
when he was pitching against the Giants in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
	``Unbelievable,'' Zeman said. ``It's a big credit to him.''  
</P>
<P>
	Stottlemyre is to pitch the first of two simulated games Tuesday  
in San Diego. He'll throw another simulated contest, then plans to 
make three minor league starts in Tucson. At least the first will 
be with the Diamondbacks' team in the Arizona Rookie League. 
</P>
<P>
	Stottlemyre decided not to undergo surgery to repair the injury  
because he wanted to play this year. Instead, he opted for a 
strenuous rehabilitation program. He worked out daily on the 
weights to strengthen the area around the injury, but wasn't able 
to begin throwing until June 22. 
</P>
<P>
	Stottlemyre was elated to have a date set for his return.  
</P>
<P>
	``You know, not only throwing a baseball for five weeks, there  
was no light at the end of the tunnel. All it was weight 
training,'' Stottlemyre said. ``Then when I started throwing, it 
was such a cautious, slow process. Every time I threw, it was 
trying to get over the next hurdle. The nice thing for me this time 
is there's light at the end of the tunnel. 
</P>
<P>
	``As long as there are no setbacks, they've got me pitching in a  
major league game. I'm real excited about that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Before he was hurt, Stottlemyre, who signed as a free agent with  
Arizona, was 4-1 with a 3.59 ERA. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
