<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Scattered thunderstorms with heavy rain and lightning moved  
through the Southern states on Saturday, while cloudy skies and 
scattered showers prevailed in the Northeast and West. 
</P>
<P>
	Isolated storms were reported in parts of Tennessee and  
Kentucky. Severe thunderstorm watches were in effect for Virginia. 
</P>
<P>
	Scattered showers were found over eastern Pennsylvania, the  
south-central border of New York state, upper New England and east 
New Hampshire. 
</P>
<P>
	The western and central Great Lakes to lower Ohio Valley were  
mainly dry and fair to partly cloudy in the afternoon. Partly 
cloudy conditions covered the Gulf States and Southeast. 
</P>
<P>
	Some storms were seen in Kansas and Missouri. The remaining  
central states were dry and mostly sunny, with partly cloudy skies 
in upper Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	It was cloudy and rainy in Washington and Oregon, eastern Idaho  
and western and upper Montana. Farther south, clouds covered a good 
chunk of central Arizona, northwestern and middle California, 
eastern Utah and western Colorado. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures Saturday in the Lower 48 ranged from a  
mid-afternoon high of 100 in Little Rock, Ark., to a morning low of 
37 in Stanley, Idaho. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
