<HEADLINE>  Singer Phil Collins Gets Married </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAUSANNE, Switzerland (AP) -- British rock star Phil Collins has  
invited more than 300 guests to celebrate his marriage to Swiss 
fiancee, Orianne Cevey, at a luxury hotel in Lausanne Saturday 
evening. 
</P>
<P>
	Collins, 48, and Cevey, 27, were married Friday in a private  
civil ceremony at Begnins, the village near Lake Geneva where the 
former Genesis drummer and singer lives, Lausanne daily Le Matin 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
	Heavy security was in place at the lakeside Hotel Beau Rivage,  
which was closed to the public for Saturday's celebrations of 
Collins' third marriage. 
</P>
<P>
	No details were made public, but Swiss media reported that stars  
including Eric Clapton, Elton John, Mark Knopfler and Collins' 
former Genesis colleagues were expected to attend. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
