</P>
<P>
	With Doyle in Hastings, England, and Lischner in Corvallis, they  
collaborated by e-mail. As one would finish something at the end of 
his day, he would e-mail it to the other, eight time zones away. 
</P>
<P>
	``The fact we never saw each other made it easier,'' Doyle says.  
``You don't sit down and have all those hours of heartache. 
</P>
<P>
	``When we started communicating with the publishers more and the  
