</P>
<P>
	A happy face means victorious in battle, a frowning face means  
defeated in battle. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a way of saying, `Don't take this all too seriously,'''  
Doyle says. 
</P>
<P>
	Doyle recommends playgoers fill out the scorecards while reading  
the play, not watching a performance. 
</P>
<P>
	``If I were sitting next to somebody trying to keep score in a  
theater, I would be furious,'' Doyle says. ``We do suggest if you 
do that, you do it at the interval.'' 
  	   	
</P>
