<HEADLINE> Two Dead in NYC Building Collapse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Two women walking through a street fair were  
killed instantly Saturday when the facade of a clothing store 
collapsed on them. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident in the New York City borough of Queens occurred  
just before 1 p.m. A third person was injured in the accident. 
</P>
<P>
	The city Buildings Department was on the scene investigating the  
collapse. There was no immediate report on what caused the 
accident, said police spokeswoman Detective Madelyne Colon. 
  	   	
</P>
