<HEADLINE> Royal Flush Hanover Wins at Yonkers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	YONKERS, N.Y. (AP) -- Royal Flush Hanover, a $35,000 supplemental  
entry, and Island Fantasy turned in identical times of 1:54 1-5 in 
winning the eliminations in the $405,325 Art Rooney Pace at Yonkers 
Raceway on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Driven by Luc Ouellette, Royal Flush Hanover, the only  
supplement in the two races that determined the eight finalists for 
the July 31 championship, turned in fractions of 27 flat, 56.2 and 
1:24.1 in romping to a six and one-quarter length victory over Old 
Buzzard. 
</P>
<P>
	Bolero Master took third, but Union Station, which broke stride  
at the start and finished fourth, was disqualified. 
Justanotherpoorboy moved up from fifth to advance to the finals. 
</P>
<P>
	Island Fantasy, who was the Pacer of the Year as a 2-year-old in  
1998, overtook Falcons Icon, who led all the way until the stretch. 
The quarters were 28.1, 57.1 and 1:25.2 with Hall of Fame driver 
Mike Lachance handling the reins. 
</P>
<P>
	Washington V C and Artistic Freedom also passed Falcons Icon,  
which held on for the fourth and final spot. 
  	   	
