<HEADLINE> DiMaggio Friend Blasts Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- In life, late baseball Hall of Famer Joe DiMaggio  
closely guarded his privacy. Now some of his confidential medical 
charts have been found mixed with hospital documents being used in 
a court case. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is such an invasion of privacy for such a private man,''  
said Morris Engelberg, DiMaggio's close friend and attorney. 
``What's more sacred than your hospital records?'' 
</P>
<P>
	The records were among medical papers submitted as evidence in  
the case of a mother accused of deliberately making her daughter 
sick to get attention and sympathy for herself. 
</P>
<P>
	DiMaggio and Kathy Bush's daughter, Jennifer, were both treated  
at Memorial Regional Hospital in Hollywood, Fla. DiMaggio died in 
March. 
</P>
<P>
	The mistake was discovered Friday when attorneys for both sides  
gathered to view the hospital documents. Mrs. Bush's attorneys are 
now arguing the mistake is evidence the hospital mishandled the 
girl's records. 
</P>
<P>
	The hospital called the mistake a clerical error, apologized for  
the sloppiness and said it is reviewing its procedures to prevent 
other mistakes. 
</P>
<P>
	Engelberg said he plans to sue to obtain DiMaggio's records from  
the hospital to keep them safe. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
