<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Irishman Plays American Sheriff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- For ``Lake Placid'' costar Brendan Gleeson,  
playing a small-town American sheriff was tough. The Irishman 
thinks sounding American is one of his greatest challenges. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm quite nervous about the accent thing,'' Gleeson says in  
the July 23 issue of Entertainment Weekly. ``At home I could go 
county by county. But a standard American accent is actually the 
hardest thing to do.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Gleeson, who starred in ``The General,'' a film dealing with  
Irish gangster Martin Cahill, said playing the notorious thug was 
touchy. 
</P>
<P>
	``I didn't want to dance on anybody's grave,'' Gleeson said.  
``There are still people hobbling about Dublin in pain from things 
he did.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A schoolteacher before his acting career took off in 1990,  
Gleeson is currently doing another ``foreign'' accent, playing an 
English villain in the sequel, ``Mission Impossible 2,'' which is 
being filmed in Australia. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
