<HEADLINE> 15 Hurt in Gay Pride Parade Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- A tear gas canister was thrown into the crowd  
watching a Lesbian and Gay Pride parade Saturday, injuring more 
than a dozen people, a city fire spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
	No arrests were made.  
</P>
<P>
	About 15 people were treated at the scene for eye and skin  
irritations. Three others, including a woman with asthma, were 
taken to a local hospital with minor injuries, fire spokesman Bob 
Macy said. 
</P>
<P>
	Thousands of people were watching the 25th annual parade when a  
big puff of smoke erupted at about 1 p.m., sending people 
scurrying. 
</P>
<P>
	``I thought it was just smoke, some kind of fire,'' said Steve  
Danaemiller, who was treated at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
	The parade was delayed about 15 minutes as police unsuccessfully  
tried to find the attacker. 
  	   	
</P>
