<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil 4, Germany 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GUADALAJARA, Mexico (AP) -- Alex scored twice as a young  
Brazilian team scored four goals in the second half to beat Germany 
4-0 in the opening game of the Confederations Cup Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The first goal came in minute 16 of the second half. An  
off-balance Ronaldinho headed the ball into the center of the 
field, and Ze Roberto hit a drive straight off goalie Jens 
Lehmann's hands. 
</P>
<P>
	Ten minutes later, Ronaldinho scored on a rebound of his own  
penalty kick. Alex, a 21-year-old, scored the final two goals. 
</P>
<P>
	Germany had few scoring opportunities, and most were shot wide.  
Its best chance came in minute 39 of the first half, when a long 
shot bounced off the hands of Brazilian goalie Dida and Michael 
Preetz tried to tap the ball in. Brazilian defender Evanilson 
cleared it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
