<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 'Unruly' Passenger Held for Fracas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- An airline passenger roaming the aisles became  
unruly when asked to return to his seat, injuring four people and 
forcing the plane to divert course, officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
	Among those hurt on the Delta Airlines flight that left Los  
Angeles late Friday was a 17-month-old child who suffered minor 
burns from spilled coffee. 
</P>
<P>
	The unidentified passenger, described only as a Vietnamese  
national in his 30s, was taken into custody by Las Vegas police, 
said McCarran International Airport spokesman John Hanks. The man's 
brother was held for questioning. 
</P>
<P>
	Flight 194 was initially bound for Atlanta, but diverted course  
to Las Vegas to remove the passenger and treat the injured. 
</P>
<P>
	``The individual who had the altercation was up and moving  
around when he wasn't supposed to be and they tried to seat him. He 
tried to get past the beverage cart and just got violent,'' Hanks 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Airline beverage and food carts typically block the entire  
aisle. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy burned by coffee was treated at University Medical  
Center and released. The others hurt, a flight attendants and two 
female passengers, were treated at the scene for minor cuts and 
bruises. 
</P>
<P>
	The flight resumed its trip to Atlanta after more than a  
three-hour delay. 
</P>
<P>
	Delta Airlines did not immediately returned a phone call from  
The Associated Press seeking comment this morning. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
