<HEADLINE> Fusion 1, MetroStars 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Edwin Gorter scored on a 30-yard  
free kick in the 84th minute to lift the Miami Fusion to a 1-0 
victory over the struggling New York-New Jersey MetroStars on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Gorter's second goal of the season sailed into the upper right  
corner of the net after MetroStars midfielder Mike Sorber had 
fouled Welton. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was Miami's third in a row, tying a club record set  
last year. The Fusion is now 7-12 with 17 points in the MLS Eastern 
Conference. The MetroStars have lost three straight and 12 of their 
last 14. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars, who have the fewest goals scored and most goals  
allowed in MLS, have a league low nine points. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars debuted two new foreign players in Columbian  
striker Henry Zambrano and Yugoslavian midfielder Sasa Curcic, but 
couldn't generate much offense. 
</P>
<P>
	Their two best chances came in the second half. Lawrence  
Lozzano's long shot was stopped by Miami goalkeeper Garth Lagerwey 
in the 74th minute and a hard shot by Brian Kelly from Curcic that 
was turned away by Lagerwey in the 83rd minute. 
  	   	
</P>
