<HEADLINE> Redskins Re-Sign LB Ken Harvey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ASHBURN, Va. (AP) -- Four-time Pro Bowl linebacker Ken Harvey  
agreed to return to the Washington Redskins as a backup Friday, 
signing a one-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
	Harvey was bothered by hamstring and knee injuries last season  
and had only two sacks in 11 games. He was due to count $2 million 
against the salary cap this season and would have been released had 
he not agreed to a new contract with a substantial pay cut. 
</P>
<P>
	His new contract will pay him $500,000, but he could earn as  
much as $2 million in incentives if he regains his starting role 
and has another Pro Bowl season. 
</P>
<P>
	Harvey, who first signed with Washington as an unrestricted free  
agent in 1994, will be used primarily as a third-down pass rusher. 
Third-year player Greg Jones will replace Harvey as the starting 
strong side linebacker. 
  	   	
</P>
