<HEADLINE> Que Belle Wins Osunitas Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Que Belle charged from last place to pull  
ahead in the last stride to defeat Bella Chiarra in the $111,300 
Osunitas Handicap at Del Mar on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Que Belle, sent postward at odds of 4-1 in the field of eight  
older fillies and mares, nosed out Bella Chiarra in a narrow photo 
finish. 
</P>
<P>
	Bella Chiarra led from the start and was within yards of the  
wire when it was passed by the late-charging winner ridden by Eddie 
Delahoussaye. 
</P>
<P>
	Cyrillic was in third place, nearly two lengths behind the  
runnerup. 
</P>
<P>
	Que Belle, the Canadian-bred daughter of Seattle Dancer, ran the  
1 1/16 miles in 1:41 3/5. 
</P>
<P>
	Her fifth win in 11 career efforts, Que Belle earned $66,780 and  
returned $10.20, $5.80 and $4.40. Bella Chiarra returned $6.00 and 
$4.00, and Cyrillic had $6.40. 
  	   	
