<HEADLINE> Gonzales Sits After Jamming Wrist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Texas outfielder Juan Gonzalez sat  
out of the Rangers' game at Tampa Bay on Saturday night after 
jamming his right wrist the night before. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez, hitting .310 with 25 homers and 85 RBIs, was hurt  
sliding into third base in the fourth inning of the Rangers' 11-8 
win Friday night against the Devil Rays. 
</P>
<P>
	``If he's ready tomorrow (Sunday), fine,'' Texas manager Johnny  
Oates said. ``If not, hopefully he'll be ready for Tuesday.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Oates said pitcher Mike Morgan, who left Friday's game with a  
bruised right forearm after being hit by Bubba Trammell's line 
drive in the second, should make his next scheduled start Thursday. 
However, Oates did not completely rule out the right-hander missing 
the start. 
</P>
