<HEADLINE> On a Soapbox Wins at Belmont </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	New York (AP) -- Jerry Bailey continued his recent domination of  
Belmont Park's $350,000 Coaching Club American Oaks when he rode On 
a Soapbox to a 4 1/4 length victory in Saturday's 83rd running of the 
race. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the third time in its last four runnings that Bailey rode  
the CCAO winner. He took the 1996 running aboard My Flag, then 
guided Banshee Breeze to her victory last year. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the second in three starts this year for On a  
Soapbox, a daughter of Mi Cielo from the Stage Door Johnny mare, 
Makin a Statement. It was also her first stakes win in six lifetime 
starts. 
</P>
<P>
	On a Soapbox covered 1 1/2 miles in 2:29:1 on the fast track to  
earn $210,000 and return $11.80, $3.20 and $2.10. Dreams Gallore 
paid $2.30 and $2.10 and Strolling Belle was $2.10 to show. 
  	   	
